1 out of every 3 girls are molested by a family member~facts 
look around the room& count the girls and know at least one has had it happen~men who are sexual predators, cousins, uncles, mothers’s boyfriends, touching, hugging on developed and any young girls, friendly kiss when we meet, rubbing up against, glaring with lust at them,gifting begins with candy,~these molesters are never strangers. they prey on and manipulate a girls innocence. there are usually others in the home who suspect something is going on but don’t want to believe it and ultimately say nothing. that’s considered aiding a criminal act. the sad  part is these girls usually are fond of the /family/friend predator who takes advantage of this. the don’t tell shhhhh allows it to continue. not all girls become withdrawn. some become attached to the predator as we have seen in many cases. almost every girl i know and every girl has many friends who have all been molested as a small child or as a teen by a family member. most of these girls tell and are not believed. others don’t. if you suspect this is happening to some girl and do nothing, you are just as guilty. the evil that men do😡 goldengirl psa~ if you wanna comment please do.. perhaps it happened to you or someone you know~ #metoo we can’t protect predators, we gotta save the children✨✨

text:
we would like to invite you to come see our play today at 8:00pm and tomorrow sunday at 3:00pm 
it is a experimental, avant garde and surreal performance. we use a combination of sounds, movement and music. citizens of the gray or this dark thing that sleeps in me is a theatrical production generated by the curiosity of how the relationship between man and woman has evolved throughout the years and how this relationship has become a struggle for power; a fight to death where there can be only one winner. 
the play portrays a world which is deeply correlated with the the #metoo movement!

there is no dialogue, nor text in this play. it traspases  language  barriers in such a way that any person from any country can understand it, given its universal codes.

at the theater for the new city, ny. 
dates: nov. 9th-25th
visit: https://bit.ly/2nfevgd to get your tickets now.
www.citizensofthegray.com #actor #theatre #creandoco #nyc

text:
warning: sexual assault/harassment/rape

so i can say that college can be a rough ride. first semester i had 2 tas, one for chemistry lab and one for chemistry theory. i thought the one from my theory class was pretty cute, we spent a lot of time together because i couldn't make his office hours so we would tirelessly go through all the homework questions together in the library. i was talking to him after an exam review one day, he sits next to me and tells me his sister was going to buy a perfume that smells of me. after i got through that class he would still stare at me, my friends would point out a guy looking at me when we were in random places, and there he would be. he finally graduated last year. my other ta was less mild, we joked around in our lab section, i would email him about lab reports at random times. he then gave me his number over the school email. he wasn't done when the semester ended. he would text me over winter break and started insinuating that i needed to blow him. i stopped talking to him after that. i showed up to class after winter break and he was my ta again, and he looked so smug. i've calculated those chances, it was around 1000th of a percent. i avoided office hours, but i was too scared to change sections because the only one i could make was in the same room with a different ta. i was scared to tell him i had a boyfriend because i thought he would fail me. he even had the guts to email me the start of the year after. that was when it started getting worse. during my first semester i met a guy, he was in my math discussion and lecture. i finally asked him for his name because he was giving me answers i didn't ask for and kept sitting next me in all our joint classes. he asked me to study physics, i told him no. one day i was studying at the library, i came back from the bathroom and he was sitting next to my desk. he told me he knew which floor i was on and deduced where i sat by looking at the angles on my instagram picture. (1/3)  #nomore #metoo #metoomovement
name: #metoo

text:
duality: "church house confessions" explores the inner battle we all face. saint or sinner? fight or flight? love or fear? we are tested every day of our lives. the universe asks us what we will do with what we have. the experience is uniquely our own. in that realization, shouldn't we see we're essentially the same? 
in these trying times, it's so important to remember where we came from and the privilege we all have in varying degrees. it's easy to point to those who have "more." but for someone else(that closeted gay kid, that rape victim who chose silence out of fear, that refugee whose family was ripped apart, that parent who lost a child to gun violence, or family that lost everything in a raging fire or flood) we are fortunate. i constantly have to remind myself that i am lucky to have what i have, even when it's far from my  projected goal. grappling with that duality. that reminder to stop and appreciate the present vs the nagging obsession with a future. so many people are in my thoughts right now. but thinking (and praying) aren't helping anyone. if you can, give to those communities who need it. volunteer, donate and speak up and vote. stay vigilant, fam✊

i've joined play it forward, which allows artists to donate their songs to charity. 100% of proceeds from downloads will go to communities in need. check out my profile(link in bio), download a track and give back all at the same time! i hope to find other artists to join me in making a larger impact, through collaborations, remixes and live performances. if you're a producer, musician or artist in the bay area and interested, please pm me❤️
.
.
"there is no dreaming too big. what people can do together is so much more powerful than what they can do by themselves" .
.

text:
bringing awareness of abuse to the forefront.
it’s not gender biased or age biased. abuse is not okay!! the statistics from the australian institute of health and welfare report that one in five women and one in twenty men are sexually abused or threatened after the age of fifteen. one in six girls and one in nine boys are abused during childhood and early adolescence. 
this is a shocking reality in our communities across australia.  how many of us are truly aware of the impact this has on not only the individual but society as a whole? 
we are putting together a book on the impact of trauma and abuse in childhood, and the ongoing effect it has on the mind, body and soul. 
this is the story of one woman’s account of the events that shaped her world. the enormity of her story will bring awareness and inspiration to others that have been touched by the crime of abuse. 
i believe when we stand together as a community, we stand stronger, dignified, and powerful. let’s break the silence! #itsnotokay.

jag tog väldigt illa vid mig av den här händelsen. var en man i 60 års åldern som efter ett samtal jag inte förstod mycket av pga språket. denna man är min elev. detta hände efter han hade pratat klart. slängde armarna runt mig och pussade mig på huvudet..
jag jobbar som trafiklärare på tungt. det är nästan bara män som elever.
jag måste alltid hävda mig, visa att jag kan för att få respekt. jag är ung och jag är kvinna. han hade aldrig gjort så mot en man.
ringde min sambo, han förstod inte så förminskade allt ist. tack så mycket. han förstår inte. så trött på den här skiten.

text:
here is a game. never have i ever felt like saying no to giving someone my number was going to put my life in jeopardy. i am not shocked when i hear about murders such as mary spears a woman who was gunned down after saying no (she had a fiance present at the time of her murder not that it mattered). i'm not shocked because i choose to take the wool from my eyes and see the violence of men that exist in this world. i choose to listen and believe the stories of women with a #metoo or not. now i know not all men are like this but all men are capable and more than enough lives are lost to the ones who do so i hope i don't get any of those comments. even my wife has a horrifying story that makes my blood boil with rage. it touches so many women in our lives and thus it is our problem as men, it is our problem because we keep doing it and perpetuating these disgusting acts on women. what can we do to stop it? well first stop pretending it is made up when a woman tells these stories. look at yourself in the mirror and realise your part in it. educate yourself and stand up. you are not entitled to anyone elses body but your own. i feel so much sorrow in my heart for this shit and i hope people google search mary spears, or maren sanchez and learn about these very true situations where life has been senslessly stolen due to misogyny and entitlement .
#colormyflaws #violence #bodypositive #art #artoftheday #mysogony
name: I.D
tweet_full:
here is a game. never have i ever felt like saying no to giving someone my number was going to put my life in jeopardy. i am not shocked when i hear about murders such as mary spears a woman who was gunned down after saying no (she had a fiance present at the time of her murder not that it mattered). i am not shocked because i choose to take the wool from my eyes and see the violence of men that exist in this world. i choose to listen and believe the stories of women with a #metoo or not. now i know not all men are like this but all men are capable and more than enough lives are lost to the ones who do so i hope i do not get any of those comments. even my wife has a horrifying story that makes my blood boil with rage. it touches so many women in our lives and thus it is our problem as men, it is our problem because we keep doing it and perpetuating these disgusting acts on women. what can we do to stop it? well first stop pretending it is made up when a woman tells these stories. look at yourself in the mirror and realise your part in it. educate yourself and stand up. you are not entitled to anyone elses body but your own. i feel so much sorrow in my heart for this shit and i hope people google search mary spears, or maren sanchez and learn about these very true situations where life has been senslessly stolen due to misogyny and entitlement .

text:
depression isn’t beautiful.
-
it isn’t long train rides listening to music and writing poetry.
it isn’t smoking cigarettes and writing love letters.
-
it’s staying in and losing track of time and days. it’s the same pyjamas worn way longer than they should be. it’s not washing because you can’t find the energy to turn the shower on because what’s the point. it’s greasy hair, spotty skin. it’s not eating or eating too much. its losing jobs, losing opitunities. it’s therapy twice a week holding on to that thread of hope that it will actually do something and change your mind because time is running out. 
it’s sitting on the kitchen floor wishing you were someone else, anyone!
it’s not calling or texting your friends or family back. it’s losing your friends. it’s your mum calling you leaving voicemails begging you to pick up the phone so she can hear your voice to know you’re still alive.
-
stop romanticising depression.
-
depression isn’t beautiful.
( i’m not currently struggling with depression i’m just addressing a stereotype and breaking the stigma ❤️)

text:
öncelikle bu tarihte, 10 kasım'da cumhuriyetimizin kurucusu mustafa kemal atatürk'ü bir kez daha saygıyla anıyorum ve bir kadın olarak bir kez daha minnet duyuyorum.
house of cards'ı bilenler bilir. netflix yapımı, beyaz saray politikasını müthiş bir drama etkisi ile ekrana getiren bir dizi. 
bugün dizinin son ve 6. sezonunu izlerken fark ettiğim bazı şeyleri (nedense) paylaşmak istedim. 
son sezonda, 5 sezondur izleyicileri frank underwood rolüyle ekrana kilitleyen kevin spacey, bildiğiniz gibi 14 yaşında bir çocuğa zamanında cinsel tacizinin ortaya çıkması gibi çeşitli suçlamalar ile dizinin kadrosundan çıkarıldı. hollywood'da weinstein skandalı ve akabinde #metoo hareketiyle başlayan ünlü oyuncuların itirafları ise kadınların kariyerlerinde yaşadıkları sıkıntıları bir kez daha gösterdi. son sezonu, son derece önyargısız olarak hala izliyorum. (5.bölümü yeni bitirdim) frank underwood'un gidişi sonrası eşi, #claireunderwood un kadin başkan olarak yükselişi, ve rolü canlandıran @robingwright ın kadın yapımcı olarak da yer aldığı dizideki kadınların politikada yükselişi tabii olması gereken... ancak dizinin 6. sezonu ile çok fazla yorum okuduktan sonra bir kez daha emin oldum ki, kevin spacey'nin 14 yaşındaki bir çocuğa cinsel tacizinin ortaya çıkmasıyla başlayan bir soruşturma sonrası, dizi/futbol vs fanatizminin yanında konuya sağlikli bi̇r i̇nsan olarak bakmanın çoook daha önemli olduğu bir kez daha ortada. kevin space, çok iyi bir oyuncu olabilir ama ruhen yaralı/sapık olduğunu değiştirmez. i̇şte tam bu noktada futbol, dizi vs gibi "bolca ünlü içeren" alanlardaki fanatiklerin baktığı gibi tam tersi açıdan bakarsak "sapık olabilir ama iyi bir oyuncu/futbolcu"gibi bir bakış açısı yoğun ki en tehlikelisi de bu. bugün yine kadına şiddet haberlerine konu olan (bkz. ahmet kural, bkz. ushan çakır gibi sabıkalı) ön plandaki isimler yine gündem olmaya devam ediyor ve bu bakış açısına göre de devam edecekler! bir kadın olarak şunun altını çizmek istiyorum. çağın gidişatına bakılırsa kadınlar düşünüldüğünden çok daha fazla çalışmak ve kendilerini kanıtlamak zorunda. biz kadınlar için bu, maalesef kötü haber ancak ümitsiz de değilim.

text:
you’re powerful. you’re damn brave. you’re not always certain about what needs to be done, but you’re sure as hell committed to your truth. and you’re the kind of woman who knows that it’s just not enough to rise individually anymore—in order to truly come into ourselves, we need to rise together. as a connected sisterhood.⠀
.⠀
this is a scary—and a pivotal—time for women everywhere. and like most of us, you’ve probably had two contradictory experiences in the era of #metoo and #timesup: the catharsis of sharing your story or listening to and supporting another woman’s...and the shutdown that comes from a society that’s scared shitless of women claiming their stories and power.⠀
.⠀
at wf1, no matter how scary and messed-up things might look on the outside, we’re absolutely committed to the long game of inner transformation—story by story, woman by woman. we believe that when women just like you claim their voices, we create a world in which all women’s experiences are validated and honored.⠀
.⠀
share your story at womenforone.com/share 💜⠀
⠀
#pivotaltime #shareyourstory #womenforone #womenempoweringwomen #truthteller

text:
👑💛💙❤👑
#missearth2018
director de miss earth españa hace un comunicado de debut y despedida al concurso miss earth.
marcel castellanos, director de miss earth españa, le dice adiós al miss earth después del escándalo de explotación sexual destapado por candidatas del miss earth 2018, 2017 y 2016. y aún falta más por salir a la luz. de este escándalo aún queda mucha tela por cortar.
.
las chicas y padres deberían pensar muy bien al desear representar a ecuador en este concurso hasta que este escándalo se aclare y puedan mostrar que se pueda confiar en ellos. lo digo pues hasta ahora en todas las declaraciones de las chicas han denunciado acoso durante el concurso por parte de sponsors, las llevaban a eventos privados con estos personajes, a bailar en yates, cenas privadas y cuando ellas se quejaban el personal de la organización les aconsejaba que fueran “pacientes y amables” con estos patrocinadores. que cochinada es esa? tener que soportar acoso sexual y que te lo tengas que aguantar por el siempre hecho de agradar a unos viejos con dinero y no enojar a la organización para no quedarte fuera del top, eso es terrible. 
como lo dice marcel castellanos “no me presto para estas sinverguenzaras mucho más aún cuando esta esta rodeado de presunta trata de blancas.
por algo osmel sousa, el zar de la belleza, dejo ese concurso y lo llamo concurso de cuarta!! @zardelabelleza.
.

👑💛💙❤👑
#missearth2018
director de miss earth españa hace un comunicado de debut y despedida al concurso miss earth.
marcel castellanos, director de miss earth españa, le dice adiós al miss earth después del escándalo de explotación sexual destapado por candidatas del miss earth 2018, 2017 y 2016. y aún falta más por salir a la luz. de este escándalo aún queda mucha tela por cortar.
.
las chicas y padres deberían pensar muy bien al desear representar a ecuador en este concurso hasta que este escándalo se aclare y puedan mostrar que se pueda confiar en ellos. lo digo pues hasta ahora en todas las declaraciones de las chicas han denunciado acoso durante el concurso por parte de sponsors, las llevaban a eventos privados con estos personajes, a bailar en yates, cenas privadas y cuando ellas se quejaban el personal de la organización les aconsejaba que fueran “pacientes y amables” con estos patrocinadores. que cochinada es esa? tener que soportar acoso sexual y que te lo tengas que aguantar por el siempre hecho de agradar a unos viejos con dinero y no enojar a la organización para no quedarte fuera del top, eso es terrible. 
como lo dice marcel castellanos “no me presto para estas sinverguenzaras mucho más aún cuando esta esta rodeado de presunta trata de blancas.
por algo osmel sousa, el zar de la belleza, dejo ese concurso y lo llamo concurso de cuarta!! @zardelabelleza.
.

text:
denna vecka för ett år sedan var en febrig,sömnlös rörelse framåt.
vi visste att vi satt på en bomb som skulle detonera och förändra vårt samhälle för alltid.
vilket den gjorde. vi namngav ingen för vi vet att detta sker överallt varje dag på alla arbetsplatser och i alla samhällen.
vi vill förändra strukturen som gjort detta möjligt och för det krävs samarbete.
tack alla modiga systrar!
europa backar in i framtiden och vi får inte glömma att våra landvinningar och mikrosegrar är tunna som is. närsomhelst kan allt tas i från oss.
stå stadigt,skrik högre och organisera er. eller- stay forever silent.
mäktet folks. mäktet. 
swipea.
#tystnadtagning #equality#humanrights#feminism #metoo#womensrights #timesup #mäktet #useyourplatform @tystnadtagning.silenceaction

text:
news flash: if you’re waiting for someone to show up and save you from this chaotic world as your knight in shining armor you will never be quite as satisfied as if you show up for yourself.•
•
you are your hero. 
you know yourself better than anyone. 
you know all your thoughts, weaknesses, areas for opportunity and growth. 
you know how far you’ve come. 
you know your every secret, desire, dream and passion.•
•
love exists. 
passion is out there. 
but the truth is love is just so much more incredible when you love yourself first. other people really dig that shit. •
•
the right people really dig it when you show up to the relationship with your own set of standards, self discipline and acceptance. it means they just get to add to it rather than repair or make up for past shit they didn’t even have a thing to do with.•
•
own your story. 
be your own person first. 
and slay this mother fucken day with all your magic. 🦄🌈🙌🏼

text:
join us today for the second annual #metoo survivors' march at #hollywood and highland!
.
➡schedule
12-1pm opening speeches and performances
1-2pm we march 💥
2-3pm closing speeches and performances
#metoomarch international is holding space today for the victims of the woolsey fire currently raging throughout ventura and los angeles counties, and the victims of the recent shooting at the #borderlinebar in #thousandoaks. the victims are members of our communities. we recognize that the changing environmental conditions have caused disasters such as the fires to become increasingly worse and me too march international stands with all victims of natural disaster and climate change, recognizing that mass movement of people can often result in chaotic scenarios where people are victimized in various ways. in addition, me too march international recognizes that lax gun laws and lapses in mental health care have led to thousands of unnecessary gun deaths each year, and me too march international supports all efforts to expand mental health support.
.
today, we ask attendees to carry a white rose while we march, in order to symbolize our solidarity with the victims and our hope for a better future.
.
.
.
.

text:
------------------------------------------------
part 2 of 2
------------------------------------------------
approximately 73%*** of rape victims don’t identify their rapes until much later. 
it didn’t have happen that way. i could have known what to look for, how to know when a situation has gone from bad to worse. i could have been educated, warned, something-anything. but i wasn’t, most of us aren’t. we buy the stereotypes and the preconceived notions the media sells us. but we don’t have to. we can make a difference. i can make a difference. telling my story, one year later, is like reliving each horrifying moment, but i need to do it. i couldn’t stop him from destroying me that night, but maybe i can empower someone else to stand up and be heard when they say ‘no.’ #sexualharassment #sexualabuse #rape #rapeculture #rapesurvivor #sexualassault #survivor #staystrong #metoo #metoomovement #metooindia #opendialogue #letustalk #shareyourstory

text:
i have officially began the process of becoming a sane nurse. 1 of 8 classes done. onto class 2. for those that don’t know what sane stands for, it stands for: sexual assault nurse examiner. this area holds close to my heart. -
“i may be only one person, but i can be one person who makes a difference.”
-
• only 5-20% of sexual assaults are actually reported. • 80% of victims are assaulted by a known acquaintance. • sexual assault occurs in 10-14% of all marriages. • sexual assault is not just forcible rape, sexual assault is any type of sexual behavior or contact where consent is not freely given or obtained and is accomplished through force, intimidation, violence, coercion, manipulation, threat, deception, or abuse of authority. -
sexual assault happens, and way more often than any of us care to admit. it’s sad, but there are resources and people there to help and support you. don’t be afraid to speak out or speak up ❤️.
-
#sane #sanenurseinthemaking #domesticviolenceawareness #nomeansno #ernurse #traumanurse #psychnurse #metoo

നിങ്ങൾക്ക് അറിയാമോ ഞങ്ങളെക്കുറിച്ചു.. ഞങ്ങൾ അനുഭവിക്കുന്ന ചൂഷണങ്ങളെ കുറിച്ച്, അനീതികളെ കുറിച്ച്.. അതും 50 വര്ഷത്തെ പാരമ്ബര്യം അവകാശപ്പെടുന്ന കേരളത്തിലെ തന്നെ ഏറ്റവും വലിയ university കളിൽ ഒന്നായ  calicut university യിൽ നിന്നും. ഞാനും ഒരു victim ആണ് btech calicut university victim, ഞങ്ങൾ ഒത്തുചേരുകയാണ് 12th nov. 2018 (monday) calicut univesity യിൽ.  ഞങ്ങൾ അനുഭവിക്കുന്ന ചൂഷണങ്ങൾക്ക് എതിരെ.. ഞങ്ങൾക്ക് അവകാശപ്പെട്ട നീതിക്കായി.. 💪

നിങ്ങൾ ഒരു btech calicut university victim ആണോ, അണിചേരൂ ഞങ്ങളോടൊപ്പം. •+ result publish ചെയാൻ calicut university എടുക്കുന്ന സമയം 1 വർഷം ( നിലവിൽ btech course കൾ  ktu ഏറ്റെടുത്തതിനു ശേഷവും സ്ഥിതിയിൽ മാറ്റം ഇല്ല ) •+ ഒരു sem. ലെ exam വീണ്ടും എഴുതണമെങ്കിൽ നീണ്ട 14 മാസത്തെ കാത്തിരുപ്പ്. (മറ്റു university കളിൽ 4 മാസത്തിനുള്ളിൽ result publish ചെയുകയും 6 മാസത്തിനുള്ളിൽ supplementary exam conduct ചെയുകയും ചെയുന്നു. ) •+ supplementary exam conduct ചെയ്തതിനു ശേഷം revaluation result publish ചെയുക,  2018 ൽ pass out ആയ btech വിധ്യര്തികളെ മാത്രമായി internal improvement scheme ൽ നിന്നും ഒഴിവാക്കപ്പെടുക 
എന്നിങ്ങനെ ഒട്ടനവധി  അന്ഗീകരികാൻ കഴിയാത്ത നിലപാടുകൾ ക്ക് എതിരെ, നമുക്ക് ഒത്തുചേരാം 12th നവംബർ 2018 calicut university ൽ. ➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖

text:
تمجید فرهادی از عضو ایرانی آکادمی نوبل ادبیات
_
اصغر فرهادی با حضور در بیست ونهمین جشنواره بین المللی فیلم «استکهلم» سوئد جایزه «ویژنری» این رویداد سینمایی را دریافت کرد.
#tehrantheatre 
اصغر فرهادی که برای کسب جایزه افتخاری جشنواره استکهلم به سوئد سفر کرده است در گفتگو با روزنامه گوتنبرگ پُست این کشور درباره نقش حساس زنان و پرداختن به زندگی روزمره زنان در فیلم‌هایش گفت: زمانی که نگارش فیلمنامه را آغاز می‌کنم، از ابتدا درباره جنسیت‌ها فکر نمی‌کنم و  در فرآیند نوشتن به تدریج جنسیت و شخصیت‌ها شکل می‌گیرند و زمانی که نقش یک زن است، تلاش می‌کنم وارد شخصیت او شوم و شرایط را از زاویه دید او نگاه کنم و این ناخودآگاهم است که به من کمک می‌کند.
_
این کارگردان برگزیده اسکار ادامه داد: در حال حاضر زنان در ایران فعال‌تر و خلاق‌تر هستند، از مردان سخت‌تر کار می‌کنند و مسئولیت بیشتری را می‌پذیرند. زنان به نسبت بیشتری در مقایسه با مردان در دانشگاه‌ها تحصیل می‌کنند و فکر می‌کنم بیشتر درباره آینده تفکر می‌کنند، در حالی که مردان بیشتر علاقه‌مند به گذشته هستند. 
_
وی در واکنش به انتخاب ژیلا مساعد نویسنده و شاعر ایرانی‌الاصل به عنوان یکی از اعضای ۱۸ نفره انتخاب برنده نوبل ادبیات نیز گفت: مصاحبه‌ای از وی را دیدم و متوجه شدم که به عضو آکادمی نوبل ادبیات درآمده است. بسیاری از هموطنان من در سایر کشورها کار دشواری برای شروع داشته‌اند و محبور بودند سخت بجنگند. ژیلا مساعد اکنون عضو آکادمی سوئد (فرهنگستان سوئد) شده است و این موضوع از صمیمم قلب باعث غرور و افتخار من است. در درجه اول به دلیل این که وی یک زن است و همچنین به این دلیل که ایرانی است. 
_
کارگردان «چهارشنبه سوری» گفت: هم‌اکنون موضوع بهبود وضعیت زنان در سینما یک مساله جهانی است و جنبش‌هایی چون #metoo در بلند مدت می‌توانند تغییراتی ایجاد کنند اما این امر زمان‌بر است. 
_
این کارگردان برنده دو جایزه اسکار همچنین درباره تاثیر سانسور بر آثارش نیز توضیح داد: سانسور مرا وادار می‌کند درباره چگونگی بیان خودم فکر کنم و باید این کار را تلویحی‌تر و بصری‌تر انجام دهم، به طوری که خود مخاطبان با قوه تخیلی و ادراک خود، آن را درک کنند. سانسور همانند صخره‌ای در جریان آب است، گرچه یک مانع محسوب می‌شود اما معمولا راهی برای گذر کردن از آن پیدا می‌کنید. برخی مواقع مانع می‌تواند نوآوری را تحریک کند چرا که شما ناگزیرید به روش‌های جدیدی برای بیان خود فکر کنید. 
@tehrantheatre 
@tehrancnema 
ادامه خبر در كامنت

فرهادی که برای کسب جایزه افتخاری جشنواره استکهلم به سوئد سفر کرده است در گفتگو با روزنامه گوتنبرگ پُست این کشور درباره نقش حساس زنان و پرداختن به زندگی روزمره زنان در فیلم‌هایش گفت : زمانی که نگارش فیلمنامه را آغاز می‌کنم، از ابتدا درباره جنسیت‌ها فکر نمی‌کنم و در فرآیند نوشتن به تدریج جنسیت و شخصیت‌ها شکل می‌گیرند و زمانی که نقش یک زن است، تلاش می‌کنم وارد شخصیت او شوم و شرایط را از زاویه دید او نگاه کنم و این ناخودآگاهم است که به من کمک می‌کند . _ این کارگردان برگزیده اسکار ادامه داد : در حال حاضر زنان در ایران فعال‌تر و خلاق‌تر هستند، از مردان سخت‌تر کار می‌کنند و مسئولیت بیشتری را می‌پذیرند . زنان به نسبت بیشتری در مقایسه با مردان در دانشگاه‌ها تحصیل می‌کنند و فکر می‌کنم بیشتر درباره آینده تفکر می‌کنند، در حالی که مردان بیشتر علاقه‌مند به گذشته هستند . _ وی در واکنش به انتخاب ژیلا مساعد نویسنده و شاعر ایرانی‌الاصل به عنوان یکی از اعضای ۱۸ نفره انتخاب برنده نوبل ادبیات نیز گفت : مصاحبه‌ای از وی را دیدم و متوجه شدم که به عضو آکادمی نوبل ادبیات درآمده است . بسیاری از هموطنان من در سایر کشورها کار دشواری برای شروع داشته‌اند و محبور بودند سخت بجنگند . ژیلا مساعد اکنون عضو آکادمی سوئد ( فرهنگستان سوئد ) شده است و این موضوع از صمیمم قلب باعث غرور و افتخار من است . در درجه اول به دلیل این که وی یک زن است و همچنین به این دلیل که ایرانی است . _ کارگردان « چهارشنبه سوری » گفت : هم‌اکنون موضوع بهبود وضعیت زنان در سینما یک مساله جهانی است و جنبش‌هایی چون در بلند مدت می‌توانند تغییراتی ایجاد کنند اما این امر زمان‌بر است . _ این کارگردان برنده دو جایزه اسکار همچنین درباره تاثیر سانسور بر آثارش نیز توضیح داد : سانسور مرا وادار می‌کند درباره چگونگی بیان خودم فکر کنم و باید این کار را تلویحی‌تر و بصری‌تر انجام دهم، به طوری که خود مخاطبان با قوه تخیلی و ادراک خود، آن را درک کنند . سانسور همانند صخره‌ای در جریان آب است، گرچه یک مانع محسوب می‌شود اما معمولا راهی برای گذر کردن از آن پیدا می‌کنید . برخی مواقع مانع می‌تواند نوآوری را تحریک کند چرا که شما ناگزیرید به روش‌های جدیدی برای بیان خود فکر کنید . ادامه خبر در كامنت

text: i have seen accounts where the entire feed is selfies with an overlay of spiritual & uplifting messages. there are times when a selfie with an uplifting overlay makes sense, but far too often, i see carefully crafted selfies or even just photographs taken of someone looking amazing made into a meme with a spiritual message over their photo. that’s when i think to myself, why don’t they just create an account specifically devoted to their self photos? and another one with awesome memes? mostly, these ladies are thin & “model-perfect” looking, and i’ll get a follow based on one of my ed-related hashtags. so as with every new follower, i click on their account to see if they are worthy of seeing me baring my soul and sharing recovery journey. most of the time, i have to block them, and so many times, i have to see these - very thing that ed looooves to use as one of my triggers. so, this is yet one more way to protect my feed, not just the things i will see, but the things that others will see about my experience in life. my precious soul. #selfies #selfiesteem #narcissisticselfie #narcissistsofinstagram #eatingdisorderrecovery #soul #selflove #healing #upliftingquotes #bodylove #empoweringwomen #mentalhealthawareness #womeninspiringwomen #empowerment #lifecoach #reinventyourself #meditation #quotestoliveby #positivememes #followers #inspirationalquotes #quotes #strongwomen #ed #fuckoffed #anorexia #striveforgreatness #selfawareness #metoo #universe thank you @sacredizeyourlife for keeping it real.
name: Lily Sauvage ידוע גם בשם שושנה

wysiadam i widzę młodą dziewczynę szarpaną, obmacywaną, obcałowywaną na siłę przez chłopaka. niemal krzyczy, żeby ją zostawił, że nie chce go znać. wiecie, ile osób zareagowało? byłam jedyna.
nic nowego.
gdy kiedyś na środku przejścia dla pieszych złodziej chciał wyrwać mężczyźnie torbę z laptopem również zareagowałam tylko ja. nie przechodziliśmy jako jedyni, ulica nie była pusta. 
zresztą doświadczyłam tego sama, gdy wiele razy byłam w podobnej sytuacji jak ta dziewczyna albo ostatnio, gdy zostałam okradziona w wagonie pełnym ludzi. dopiero po fakcie okazało się, że były osoby, które widziały dwóch podejrzanych kolesi. czemu nie sprawdziły co się dzieje? no właśnie. pomijam dwóch "mężczyzn" w sile wieku, którzy zamiast wziąć się do pracy wolą kogoś okraść. np. mnie z tygodniowej wypłaty nie śpiącej praktycznie 3 dni z rzędu, bo jakoś trzeba się utrzymać...
ale do sedna. o ile jestem w stanie zrozumieć, gdy nie reaguje kobieta, to w każdej z tych sytuacji byli "mężczyźni", którzy stali i nie reagowali. do tej pory byłam daleka od oceniania co dana płeć powinna robić, ale gdy kolejny raz poznaję "faceta", która okazuje się(wrażliwi nie czytać) męską c*pą to naprawdę miarka mi się przebrała. czy są jeszcze na tym świecie prawdziwi mężczyźni, którzy są w stanie stanąć w obronie słabszych i mają jakiejkolwiek zasady i choć trochę empatii? są w stanie z kimkolwiek normalnie rozmawiać? chociaż z tym to akurat nie tylko oni mają problem tylko całe społeczeństwo. 
zaczynam wątpić. 
i zastanawiam się, która to słaba płeć i kto ma większe jaja.

text: my curatorial moment no. 46 “secret” — ryan steadman “2 sisters” (acrylic and oil on panel circa 2004) is an early period piece where precision line and impasto were part of his oeuvre. it was during the pre-insta era where i connected with ryan on email, met up at the legendary empire diner in chelsea, and off we parted with the painting in tow. easy-peasy...stayed in contact since. as for the painting, i see the faces quite differently today and can’t help but to think of a #metoo sisterly moment of confiding and consoling. i mimic the moment with a pair of unworn socks...a little too kooky. #ryansteadman @ryansteadman #mycuratorialmoment

text: thank you for the love & support we’ve felt since the article release🎉❤️ we are sorry to say that our chalk art was washed away by georgetown university late thursday night—but we were humbled to share our message throughout campus for the one day. we recognize that it was provocative, and are truly sorry if individual survivors felt triggered, but we feel that people need to see the scope of the pain that this issue causes, and the huge extent that it affects our community members. to that end, thank you to all brave survivors who have already reached out, willing to share!! your voices now have a platform and a huge community of people who get it. keep sending your stories: the more we speak up, the more power we take back. stay tuned for updates on ig, fb, and twitter—we have some exciting actions for progress in the works❤️ love & solidarity. #metoo

text:
#metoo a b.tech calicut university victim. 
നിങ്ങൾക്ക് അറിയാമോ ഞങ്ങളെക്കുറിച്ചു... ഞങ്ങൾ അനുഭവിക്കുന്ന ചൂഷണങ്ങളെ കുറിച്ച്, അനീതികളെ കുറിച്ച്.. അതും 50 വർഷത്തെ പാരമ്പര്യം അവകാശപ്പെടുന്ന കേരളത്തിലെ തന്നെ ഏറ്റവും വലിയ university കളിൽ ഒന്നായ calicut university യിൽ നിന്നും.
.
.
ഞാനും ഒരു victim ആണ് btech calicut university victim, ഞങ്ങൾ ഒത്തുചേരുകയാണ് 12th nov. 2018 (monday) calicut university യിൽ. ഞങ്ങൾ അനുഭവിക്കുന്ന ചൂഷണങ്ങൾക്ക് എതിരെ.. ഞങ്ങൾക്ക് അവകാശപ്പെട്ട നീതിക്കായി.. 💪

നിങ്ങൾ ഒരു btech calicut university victim ആണോ? അണിചേരൂ ഞങ്ങളോടൊപ്പം!
.
.
•+ result publish ചെയാൻ calicut university എടുക്കുന്ന സമയം 1 വർഷം ( നിലവിൽ btech course കൾ  ktu ഏറ്റെടുത്തതിനു ശേഷവും സ്ഥിതിയിൽ മാറ്റം ഇല്ല )
.
.
•+ ഒരു sem. ലെ exam വീണ്ടും എഴുതണമെങ്കിൽ നീണ്ട 14 മാസത്തെ കാത്തിരുപ്പ്. (മറ്റു university കളിൽ 4 മാസത്തിനുള്ളിൽ result publish ചെയുകയും 6 മാസത്തിനുള്ളിൽ supplementary exam conduct ചെയുകയും ചെയുന്നു. )
.
.
•+ supplementary exam conduct ചെയ്തതിനു ശേഷം revaluation result publish ചെയുക,  2018 ൽ pass out ആയ btech വിദ്യാർത്ഥികളെ മാത്രമായി internal improvement scheme ൽ നിന്നും ഒഴിവാക്കപ്പെടുക എന്നിങ്ങനെ ഒട്ടനവധി അംഗീകരിക്കാൻ കഴിയാത്ത നിലപാടുകൾക്ക് എതിരെ, നമുക്ക് ഒത്തുചേരാം...
12th നവംബർ 2018 calicut university ൽ.

text:
huge energy update ::: as above so below ::: this image was taken by @wallyskalij of the la times. it’s an image of rescued llamas on zuma beach (basically malibu area) where i grew up and all my friends are from. it’s surreal indeed. let’s talk about the energy for a moment. ⁣
⁣
the kind of astrology i specialize in is soul and karmic astrology. that’s my gift and passion. however there are astrologers that focus on the current political climate as well as the collective energies and see the mirroring in the sky. it’s always a mirroring. i simply bring it down to a personal level. mundane astrologers bring it to a collective. both are an art form. ⁣
⁣
however, any astrologer understands the connection and this we can’t ignore. ⁣
⁣
jupiter the planet of expansion, abundance, growth, think big and excess, over the top... just moved out of scorpio (on thursday) where it was for a little over the last year and into the fire sign sagittarius!⁣
⁣
with jupiter in scorpio it played out exactly as astrologers predicted the energy to be but no one could have seen the exact details. that is always for us to experience on the human realm. the #metoo movement....no coincidence. jupiter (truth telling and opening) revealed the deepest darkest shadows in scorpio which is connected to sex, intimacy, transformation, death/rebirth etc. ⁣
⁣
jupiter opened up pandora’s box. that’s what it does and the cosmos once again mirrored this on earth because in case you need a reminder, astrology is the study of the movements and relative positions of celestial bodies as having an influence on human affairs and the natural world. ⁣
⁣
this is one of the most uncontained fires (sagittarius) we’ve had in california. it’s larger than life (jupiter). it’s no coincidence. you see, you can believe in astrology or not but what i always say is it still impacts you either way. ⁣
⁣
this is not the only way jupiter in sagittarius will play out at all. it’s important to understand that. this is the shadow side. there is always a shadow side to everything. we live in a world of polarity. this is earth. we are here to experience duality until we learn the balance. ⁣
⁣
when a planet changes cont below 👇

text:
sessions live 2018 - the masculinity paradox
.
what is a girl do when she really wants to watch this livestream that i’ve been looking forward to for months, but was out until 2am and doesn’t want to get up? watch while still in bed!
.
i’ve been fascinated by the vulnerability of men, and how it exists or doesn’t exist in society, and how society has a hard time making space for the trauma of others. the #metoo movement made space for women, but men also need a safe space for their trauma for our society to change.
.
i also genuinely want to know about the toxic messages that are sent to boys and men. how does this affect our relationships, our families and our society?
.
i’ll be learning about this all day!!
.
maybe i’ll run and make some coffee while they’re still on a break.

text:
canção do bandido | ópera
teatro da trindade | 8 a 18 de novembro
qua 19h | qui e sáb 21h | dom 16h30

música & direcção musical nuno côrte-real
libreto pedro mexia
encenação ricardo neves-neves

cantores andré henriques, bárbara barradas, cátia moreso, inês simões, marco alves dos santos e sónia alcobaça
coro do teatro nacional de são carlos e orquestra sinfónica portuguesa

cenário henrique ralheta
figurinos rafaela mapril 
desenho de luz luís duarte 
assistência de encenação rafael gomes e diana vaz

produção executiva força de produção
coprodução teatro da trindade inatel, teatro nacional de são carlos e temporada darcos

partindo do conto tradicional o macaco de rabo cortado, canção do bandido imagina uma personagem que não é um macaco mas um advogado, casanova dos tempos modernos, homem que acumula conquistas e as vai trocando por novas conquistas, sem pensar muito nas consequências dos seus atos. 
o casanovismo e o donjuanismo são revisitados numa época em que as guerras dos sexos (ou dos géneros) já não são o que eram, ou têm pelo menos discursos e legitimidades diferentes. coros gregos e essencialismos em tempos digitais e de #metoo? em quem devemos acreditar: no libreto, nos protagonistas, nos antagonistas, ou nas personagens que, falando em vez de cantar, contestam estes diálogos, estes tipos, esta dialética? 
de d. giovanni à música pop, dos bordões linguísticos aos jogos nonsense, as personagens de «canção do bandido» trazem para o palco tudo o que lhes ocorre, tudo o que sirva as suas estratégias ou ilustra as suas dúvidas. e os espectadores, certamente, tomam partido.

text:
*credits unknown*
he betrayed me. he broke me into a million pieces. it was as if someone had cut me open, slashed deeply into each of my organs and stitched me back up again to live a nightmare-bleeding from the inside out. i didn’t know i had become a statistic for a crime that you never hear about.

we, as a society, hear the word rape and picture a woman being attacked in a dark alley by some drifter. we, as media-educated drones, envision a college co-ed going to a party and being assaulted by a gang of frat boys. we, as women, imagine some sicko holding a knife to our throats to get what he wants. is that rape? you bet. but, all those scenarios account for only a minor 20-30% of rapes.

that leaves 80-70% of rapes that don’t fit the stereotype. huh? how can we not know what most rapes are like? that doesn’t make any sense. what we know as rape isn’t the majority. why? how can it be that so many rapes committed aren’t what we know rape to be? no one wants to talk about real rape. no one wants to put it out there for discussion. no one wants to admit that our society has a large majority of rapes that are unspeakable, let alone unthinkable. or even worse, society just doesn’t think the majority is as bad as the stereotype. if that’s the case, we’re dead wrong-every last one of us.

#sexualharassment #sexualabuse #rapeculture #rapesurvivor #rape #survivor #letustalk #opendialogue #metoomovement #metoo #metooindia #staystrong

text:
*credits unknown* 
real rape doesn’t have to be physically violent. only 5%* of completed rapes result in serious physical injury. so if the rapist didn’t hurt them, how’d they get raped? most rapes involve much more deceptive tactics to achieve the ‘final goal.’ the victim is pressured, coerced, manipulated and even tricked (lied to) into doing the will of the predator, even when they don’t want to and say no. the tactics can vary, but we’ve all heard them voiced in society, “i talked her into it”; “i wore her down”; and the infamous “no means yes.” there is no such thing as ‘convincing’ someone to have sex. while i hate to use the cliché, it’s puts it bluntly-no means no.

text:
gettin’ deap and personal 
when i first met him all the signs were there but i ignored them. when he told me his past and all of his stories i could have hear the bad but i was so willing to believe him that i didn’t notice them. i refused to see things because at that point i needed to be loved... i had no clue all the love that i was craving for was in me...
after the first couple of months he started to show his real face, but i felt stuck and found him excuses... then the real hell started... he found my flows and weakness and prayed on them... he toyed with me... i was never enough, always wrong, crazy, ugly... he manipulated me to believe he was right and i was nothing... he insulted me, forced himself on me until i was an empty shell... i thought it was my fault, he kept telling me i was the reason why he behaved in this way... he rapped my soul and my body so many time that i can’t count... now i am gone... i finally left but his worlds didn’t... i still feel like a piece of **** when i behave according to my feeling... but the worst part is for the amazing men that is by my side because he is the one that has to deal with the nightmare, crying and fearfull behavior...
however every day i gettin better thanks to him @valentin.milet.7 and to yoga... because for the very first time of my life i am unapologetically myself... so girls never let a men put you down... you are enough never forget it... 🙏🧘🏻‍♀️💚
lastly i would like to thanks @lizfair_yoga for inspiring me to share my truth and @melissa.moffet for giving me the gift put world on it thanks to her @air.and.earth meditation
~~~~
~~~~

text:
woar is grateful to have had the opportunity to participate as a host in this year on the table philly!!! our three groups of like-minded people came together at woar to discuss the topic: “broadening the #metoo dialogue and sexual violence prevention” over lunch. 
how can change happen in a community?

by communicating openly about issues we care about and come up with new ways we can work together to address them. 
great ideas and solutions came out of this year’s @onthetablephl event!!!
.
.

text:
enligt forskare krävs det sju år av aktivt arbete för att skapa kulturförändring. tystnadskulturen, machokulturen, våldtäktskulturen. aktivt arbete gott folk. det börjar med dig och mig 🙌 tagga en vän. 
#metoo #metoosweden 👀 syntolkning: samtyckesdebatten unga män och kvinnor har olika syn på den nya samtyckeslagen, enligt en sifomätning gjord på uppdrag av brottsoffermyndigheten som sveriges radio rapporterar om.  90 procent av tillfrågade kvinnor i åldrarna 18–25 är positiva till lagen, men bara 62 procent av männen.  även uppfattningen om vad som räknas som samtycke går isär: en tredjedel av männen tycker att det räknas att ligga naken med någon i sängen, jämfört med 16 procent av kvinnorna. 17 procent av killarna tycker även att det räcker att vara ihop eller följa med någon hem för att det ska vara samtycke, vilket inte stämmer i lagens mening. – det visar på hur stort behovet är av att vi pratar om frivillighet och vilket ansvar man har när man tar initiativ till sex, säger brottsoffermyndighetens generaldirektör annika öster till svt.

text:
hans montenegro - like you’ve never heard him before. always honest, pointed, insightful and brutally frank.

here are some of the memorable things that he said:

1.  on the #metoo movement. “na molestiya ako noong 13 years old ako. i didn’t feel good about not doing anything then. coming forward with my story and learnings will hopefully inspire victims to understand that there is strength in numbers and that we should support each other; and for our colleagues in power to sanction the perpetrators. “
2. on his daughter ashley (by cara subijano) i am happy that cara and i and her new partner are ok and are good co-parents with me to our daughter who has decided to stay and live with me and my wife (marilen faustino). ashley is showing inclinations of becoming a beauty queen, but i want her to train and finish her studies first. 
3. hans corrected a gma online report, “i don’t have a son by maritoni fernandez.” our conversation tonight is one for the books. watch the interview in my fb account or at the level up showbiz saturdate page.

thank you hans for the trust and the friendship all these years. it was a good updating; sa uulitin!
#levelup #showbizsaturdate #radyoinquirer

text:
looking back at the ceo: 
once upon a time there was an ambitious young lady who set her path with her head held high, strike of confidence and personality. i use to think that was me, back in those days, just landed my first job and all i wanted to do in five years is to be a ceo. well 10 years later, look at me i am nowhere close to that. 
the truth is, i could be a ceo if i dare enough to jump, i could be a ceo if i quit my current job and start my own company, i could be a ceo if my disorders doesn't bother me or even exist. i could be if.... but far from what i had ever imagined, being a ceo of myself is what i am. i am my own ceo if you count me surviving my daily struggle. i am ceo of myself when i am in control. i am my own ceo if i can be the best that i can be everyday. 
i don't need to be a ceo to proof that i completed sets of challenges for the day. i am already successful when i decide to wake up, when i decide to go forward, when i decide it's ok to be unique, when i decide to go and move along! 
maybe one day i will become a ceo of the norm, chief executive officer of a company or maybe i would be a ceo of my own home. may god bless us all.

#candoit #motivation

text:
focus now: 
now...always remember the now! never much about the past or never more about the future. always the now!

it's hard to do this when you are bipolar, because you mind keeps on running like loose cargo train. sometime it could also feel like you are in a spiral staircase that never ends. so this is when my medication regime helps. it makes me focus and it makes me focus on the now. 
my dad always tell me to stop taking those medication, but i never listen because i love him, i love my husband, my daughter, my family and i want to be in the now, to be here and to be alive. i want to make sure i can live in the moment and stop worrying about the past or the future. 
so people of the world, live in the now, live in the moment and forever cherishes the little time we have left.

name: Izza Ahmad
tweet_full:
focus now: 
now...always remember the now! never much about the past or never more about the future. always the now!

it is hard to do this when you are bipolar, because you mind keeps on running like loose cargo train. sometime it could also feel like you are in a spiral staircase that never ends. so this is when my medication regime helps. it makes me focus and it makes me focus on the now. 
my dad always tell me to stop taking those medication, but i never listen because i love him, i love my husband, my daughter, my family and i want to be in the now, to be here and to be alive. i want to make sure i can live in the moment and stop worrying about the past or the future. 
so people of the world, live in the now, live in the moment and forever cherishes the little time we have left.

text:
the future will remain unknown: 
there are just so many things we could do to achieve our goals and life targets. so many plans we could make but at the end our destiny rely with god, the creator. but i should never forget to keep on trying everyday, to be the best everyday, and to continuously do the best that i could at everything every single time so that my future would be in my palms. that is what i tell myself everyday. you can do it! strike a pose, have faith and take the journey to the unknown.

text:
we spend so much time in our left brains that we miss out on our creativity.  tap into your creativity! be creative!  there is no one way to be creative - whether it is drawing, painting, writing, singing, baking or something else.  you don’t have to be good at it to express yourself (& you can’t get good at it if you never do it!) .
.

one thing i have noticed about myself is that now that i am not so stressed out, i see nature’s colors more and they are more vibrant than ever before. (mindfulness does work! 😊). i like to capture those colors with the pics i take (and usually share here!). .

take the time to tap into your creativity! you may be surprised about what you learn about yourself 💖 .
. 📸: geordanna cordero-fields

text:
[🎧 passion podcasts, l’émission à écouter ce week-end] en trois épisodes seulement le podcast miroir miroir de jennifer padjemi est déjà devenu incontournable. les sujets qu’il traite restent encore trop rarement abordés. cette fois, la journaliste reçoit elisa rojas, avocate au barreau de paris et cofondatrice du clhee (collectif lutte et handicaps pour l’égalité et l’émancipation), pour parler de la représentation des personnes en situation de handicap dans les médias et la société, mais aussi des politiques validistes des pouvoirs publics. elisa rojas nous donne des solutions et des explications sur des situations concrètes, et le besoin urgent d’un véritablement changement quant à la situation actuelle.
🗞 http://bit.ly/revuedepresse82
➡️ lien en bio !
.
.
.

text:
look into the eyes
of your childhood
you know now
what you knew then
that child is you
remember what
you went through
how you smiled and danced
and sang anyway
but slept with a knife
under your pillow
or glued the lock
to your bedroom door
all to no avail
- laurie maren

text:
hey guys! i will be a guest panelist during howard homecoming. please come out and support!! friday, october 26, 2018 at 1:30pm
the film begins promptly at 2pm. 26 minutes in length.

an rsvp for this free event is requested at https://laloshousefilmscreening.eventbrite.com by wednesday, october 24.

the howard alumni band, bedolove, and chronicle vision present a special film screening of a 2018 student academy award winner “lalo’s house”! all are welcome to join us and witness this amazing film, meet the inspirational kelley kali, and engage in a lively and informative panel discussion following the screening. light fare and refreshments will be served by sinfully wright catering. donations are welcome.

about the award-winning documentary:
as a writer, producer, and director of “lalo’s house”, kelley kali has created a poignant film inspired by true events, telling the story of two young haitian sisters who unknowingly get trapped in a child trafficking ring. the film includes gracelle beauvais (the jamie foxx show, spider-man 2017, and white house down) who is an executive producer and actress. and, includes jimmy jean-louis from “claws”. trailer: https://vimeo.com/243611573; https://revolt.tv/videos/insider-access-women-lalos-house-detail-importance-bringing-awareness-sex-trafficking-00810db2; http://www.laloshousefilm.com/

#womenempowerment 
#womenempoweringwomen #womenempoweringgirls 
#walkinginourpose #walkinginpower #walkinginpurpose #walkinginpower #iambeautifulbecause #beatingchildsexualabuse #csa #awareness #metoo

text:
mental health is self-care
____________________________
the 6 areas of our lives that requires constant replenishing are... ——————————————————-
1.physical self-care
basic physical needs. exercise. pampering yourself. embracing your senses. doing make sure body feels good & relaxed
___________________________
2. emotional self-care
processing emotions in a healthy way. cultivating emotional intelligence. having good coping mechanisms. feeling your feelings.
____________________________
3. personal self-care
getting to know yourself. try new things. spending time alone. making time for hobbies. having goals for yourself.
__________________________
4. social self-care
getting the amount of social interaction that feels good. creating good boundaries. working on friendships.
————————————
5. spiritual self-care
figuring out your beliefs. reading books on spirituality. prayer. seeking community. challenging your spiritual ideas.
____________________________
6. practical self-care
finances. chores. healthy work boundaries.

text:
one of the lowest vibratory frequencies is shame or comparison. even the most awesome parents and spouses face this at some point. putting down the weight is important. being authentic with one and other is important so we can all move through and out of the programming  and grow our hearts in empathy and love. 💕 .
"for all those who think they are the only ones struggling. we are all dealing with similar challenges. no one is perfect or with out struggle. the worst part about parenting is when we feel alone and isolated, like no one else knows what we are going through, or beating ourselves up for not being good enough. we need more authentic sharing, more witnessing of our real home lives... it’s great to show nice pictures on line.. but we need more authentic sharing of our hard times too. family is the highest path i know, most challenging and most worth it all. i pray for all families to have the strength to stay together, rise above the struggles, yearn for and create break throughs, heal, become self realized and help others do the same. we are one human tribe, one being of divine source. may we receive the grace in stillness and surrender during the hardest of times. surrender now, allow this moment to be experienced fully as it is. perfection is revealed in silence and stopping of the following of mind." rp @phifractalfamily ❤️ #authentic#truth#metoo#youarenotalone#weallstruggle#waldorf#homeschooling#honoringourancestors#truth#surrender#selfrealization#selfinquiry#selflove#servicefromtheheart#unitehumanity#familylife#love#karma#dharma#transformation#surrender#lifewithchildren#modernfamily#ubuntufuture#phifractalfamily#yeshi_sol #authenticity #parenting #attachmentparenting #raiseyourvibration

text_retweet:
a t t i t u d e  i s  e v e r y t h i n g
.
#repost @psychicpassage .
.
💜like the true teacher he is, jupiter taught me a thing or two during his time in scorpio. .
.
.
💙having a scorpio moon opposite chiron in taurus – both square mars in aquarius – jupiter (ruler of my descendant) opened me up to deep exploration of my emotions, self-worth, and past experiences through my relationships, friendships and community.
.
.
💜i’ve been awakened to deeply ingrained generational patterns and dealt with some pretty ugly situations. i had to address the impact other people had on my emotional environment, how much power i give them, and how much i project my own negative traits as a way of protecting myself.
.
.
💙but within that struggle, i had moments of truth, learning about myself as a soul having a human experience. an experience where i found myself acknowledging the truth about myself, and understanding this about other people. people that i wanted to hate, and separate from my existence as much as possible
.
.
💜but i realised—just as i did about my own parents—that these imperfect humans struggle with their own challenges, battle their own demons, muddling through life making the best choices they can. .
.
💙i was offered a priceless piece of advice: “if you can’t change the situation, change your attitude towards it”. .
.
.
💜i focussed on why i was feeling the way i was, why i reacted the way i did, and i looked at what the possible meaning could be. .
.
.
💙that’s when i made my personal discovery; i empowered myself, let go of pain, suffering, anger, sadness, guilt. i evolved, mentally, emotionally, spiritually. .
.
💜i saw my difficulties for the lessons that they were. the anger for the freedom it offered me, the sadness for the realisation that i am moving forward & cannot possess or control the moments that pass.
.
💙thank you, jupiter. 🙏🏻 .
.

text: inspired by therapist #marisapeer watching an interview with author/entrepreneur #lewishowes on his show #theschoolofgreatness (youtube) i wrote a little note to myself 🙂 in the interview marisa talked about the main struggle we all face - the feeling of ‘i’m not enough’ - we tend to talk to ourselves negatively a lot and it’s the words we use that have a great impact on our wellbeing - she talks about how our thoughts can either heal us or kill us, quite literally too - that what we say manifests as our reality, including physical diseases. when we continuously push feelings away instead of sitting with them and feeling it, expressing it in some way and understanding them, this is when these feelings manifest in different negative ways and cause serious harm to ourselves, also impacting on others and our environment. marisa emphasised how important positive self talk is, especially to remind yourself that we are enough. as i struggle with perfectionism i find it so helpful to express myself creatively and to write things down, including little notes to myself - feeling a bit flat today so i gave myself a little reminder and hopefully it helps others too. marisa’s practice involves writing on your mirror - i am enough or on a piece of paper and sticking it around the house - a great way to remind ourselves to be kind to ourselves especially as it can be so hard sometimes, i have to really work on this after years of beating myself up massively but it’s all about the process and so worth it 🧡🌼 #trusttheprocess #perfectionism #perfect #imperfect #perfectlyimperfect #youareenough #bekind #selfkindness #selflove #selfcare #change #positiveselftalk #positivethoughts #youarenotalone #itsok #itsoktonotbeok #knowyourself #expressyourself #creative #creativeprocess #metoo #youmatter #anxietywarrior #wellbeing #feelings

text_retweet:
#repost  @animalrevenge #animalrevenge at its finest.  @standup911 compassion starts when you are able to look into the eyes of another living being and see yourself within them. remember as children we were taught to treat others as we would want to be treated. well i think we all need to connect back to that very important message. slow down time for a second and stare into the eyes of another animal and you will see them as you. they share the same emotions, they want to live and be happy and they want to protect their families. no living being will willingly give their life up. let’s think about the word humane for second. the definition of humane is having or showing compassion. now think of humane slaughter. what is humane about having throats slit, being thrown into a gas chamber or having a electric bolt to the skull. as you can tell there is absolutely nothing humane about it. keep in mind all of those imagines and wording they use to program your mind. the cows and pigs enjoying life, using words like free range. it’s all a lie. the governments are literal subsidizing animal agriculture just for it to simply exist. it’s not sustainable in any shape. from so called grass fed to factory farming. it’s all extremely toxic on every level. for the sake of your own damn self and everything around go vegan. make the connection. fight for something bigger than yourself. just because something is legal doesn’t make it morally correct.
-
#bethechange #compassion #humane #vegan #happyworldveganday #worldveganday #metoo

text:
the phycologist: 
a new type of therapy that i am trying, before this we had gone to neurologist, psychiatrist and hypnotherapist. last week we embark on something new, a phsycologist. to differentiate; a neurologist is a medical doctor that specialized in brains, psychiatrist is a medical doctor specialized in mental disorders, a hypnotherapist does not need to be a doctor but have certification in hypnoteraphy and they hypnotized you or your unconscious mind to be better, and a phsycologist is someone that uses counseling sessions and phsycotheraphy. 
so this young chap we met was kinda cool. he thaught my case was very interesting and my coping mechanism is very unique. he doesn't judge or make funny faces when me or azhar tells him stuffs that had happened. at first i was worried because he looked so young he would be more judgmental and less experienced, but because he was cool and open minded i wouldn't mind seeing him again once a week for the next 5 weeks. even if he doesn't know how to deal with me, i hope that he would do his research and figure things out before our next session. best of luck for all of us... #imok #selfhelp #tryingmybest #everydayisanewday

text:
precis som uppdrag granskning visade i onsdagens reportage om sanne så faller de patienterna med svårast problem ofta mellan stolarna. när ingen aktör har tillräckligt med resurser håller varje instans hårt i att endast utföra sitt begränsade uppdrag, systemet är därför riggat för att misslyckas. psykiatrin har inte hand om beroende, kommunen har inte hand om psykiatri och vårdplatserna på avdelningarna är färre än patienterna. även för mindre akuta problem bollas ofta patienterna fram om tillbaka. trots att det är så vanligt med samsjuklighet och att dessa patienter borde prioriteras högt så blir samsjukligheten något som ökar sannolikheten att bli avvisad. smärtrehab har inte i sitt uppdrag att behandla ptsd, psykiatrin tycker smärtan är ett hinder och primärvården tycker fallet är för komplext. det finns ingen quick fix på detta. alla instanser måste ha resurser för att kunna utföra sitt uppdrag. men det måste även till att alla instanser täcker upp för varandra och ibland ger insatser som ligger utanför ramen. vi måste sluta spela pingis med remisserna!

text:
det var en kille som jag visste om vem det var, han hade tidigare varit på och raggat på mig och min tjejkompis, vi båda hade avböjt honom.
det gick ändå något år efter det till att han dök upp igen, jag pratade/ hade legat med en kompis till honom och han visste om detta för tydligen visste alla i deras krets om detta.
han bad mig iaf komma hem till honom, minns inte varför, men det var något speciellt minns jag.
så jag gjorde det i god tro.
när jag väl kommer dit sätter han mig på sin säng (som var den enda möbeln han hade i sin lilla etta) och började kallprata, jag listar snabbt ut vart han tänkte detta skulle gå, så jag säger rakt ut att jag inte kommer ligga med honom!
han svarar att det är lugnt men ändå försöker han efter 5 minuter att få mig på rygg, jag säger igen att jag inte vill och han säger att inte heller vill. 
jag borde ju ha gått därifrån men jag stannade och frågade vad han egentligen ville prata om!
han försökte prata bort mig för att sedan försöka få ner mig på rygg i sängen igen, jag säger jag inte vill och han svarade att jag inte vet det förrens jag provat. jag ger upp så jag slutar säga något och bara följer med hans rörelser fast mitt kroppsspråk och ansikte rätt tydligt säger att jag inte vill, han kysser min hals och smeker min kropp, men jag bara ligger stilla.
han får av mig kläderna och har sex med mig fortfarande bara liggandes där.
när han är klar tar han upp telefonen och smsar en person som tydligt är hans partner om hur mycket han älskar henne.
jag ligger fortfarande där och när jag såg smset vaknade jag till ur min bubbla av att ge upp och frågar vad fan han tyckte han kunde knulla mig när han hade en tjej redan, tog på mig mina kläder och åkte hem.
han smsade 2 veckor senare och frågade om jag kunde komma förbi igen.. #intedinfetisch #metoo #vifinnsochvisyns #metoosverige
name: #InteDinFetisch

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

text:
what are you doing in your community to help prevent child sexual abuse?

don't just sympathize with victims and their parents. get up and do something about it!

ok  i understand, you don't have the skill but you have passion. passion is key! now, the next step is to get trained! 
yes, training will strengthen your passion. thank god you have an opportunity to get the necessary skills at the child sexual abuse awareness and prevention workshop taking place on 1st december 2018 in lagos.

call +2348027835885 for registration details.

thanks to @pius.adegoke and @adegokeyeni for taking the bold step to educate parents about their roles in the prevention of child sexual abuse in porthatcourt. god bless you!

text:
... & yesss i did it 💪🏽🙌🏼 . all the way to the mosque mark!👊🏽
.
.
... “running isn’t a sport for pretty “girls”...
.
.
. …it’s about the sweat in your hair and the blisters on your feet. .
.
.
... it’s about throbbing calves and cramps at midnight that are strong enough to wake the dead.
.
.
.
... it’s about getting out the door and running when the rest of the world is only dreaming about having the passion that you need to live each and every day with.
.
.
.
... it’s about being on a lonely road and running like a champion even when there’s not a single soul in sight to cheer you on.
.
.
.
... running is all about having the desire to train and persevere until every fiber in your legs, mind, and heart is turned to steel. and when you’ve finally forged hard enough, you will have become the best runner you can be. and that’s all that you can ask for. “ ... ~ paul maurer
.
.
.

borderline electra 
sat 17th nov 2018, 7pm
@footlightsuk @mediacityuk 
a play written and directed by stevie helps, including some of his own experiences in psychiatric hospitals between 2007-2011

#borderlineelectra is all about consequences, such as when people in a position of care don’t carry out their duty correctly or when relationships are abusive and the devastating affects of what can happen if these things are not prevented. the consequences of someone with power not being taken care of themselves. the consequences of government cuts play a part in the play, too. the play is about the consequences of neglect and failing to act.”
#steviehelps

text:
ostatni odcinek „ameryka express” jest zły na wielu poziomach – to obrzydliwe wykorzystanie przywileju, przedmiotowe traktowanie ludzi, całowanie osób bez ich zgody, ale też – pokaz wymuszania zgody. 
nawet w momentach, w których nie ma całowania, widzimy „targowanie się” i próby przekonania do pocałunku na przeróżne sposoby: „bo to reality show”, „bo to telewizja”, „por favor kiss my friend” itd. 
przy tej okazji przypominam, że „zgoda” wymuszona nie jest zgodą faktyczną. podobnie „zgoda” wyrażona wskutek zastraszenia lub innego wykorzystania pozycji władzy/przewagi. zgoda musi być dobrowolna, wyrażona przez wszystkie strony. consent is key. #metoo #zgoda #stopkulturzegwałtu #consent #kulturagwałtu

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
ヴェノム #映画
マーベルの流れをくむアメコミ ヒーローもの。
とはいえ、制作はソニーということで、アベンジャーズではなくスパイダーマン寄りということのようです。
原作ではスパイダーマンの敵役だったそうで、本作ではそのあたりをどう描いているのか…については、あえて触れません。
作品としての感想は、残念ながら退屈な凡作でした。
ヴェノムの宿主となるエディが、とにかくダメな人。フリーのジャーナリストという設定なんだけど、お前は駆け出しか？みたいな雑な取材しかしていないように見えるんです。
だから、序盤の展開も自業自得にしか見ないし、そのあとの展開も「なんで、この程度のジャーナリストに、そんな大役を？」って不自然に思えてしまう。
弁護士の元カノに愛想尽かされるのも当然…と思っていたから、後半の展開には愕然。思春期の若者が抱きがちな、身勝手な妄想レベル。
昨今の #metoo 運動を一切無視するかのような、ステレオタイプだらけ（男にとって都合のいい存在）の女性像には、心底ガッカリです。
ダークヒーローという設定ゆえか、夜のシーンが多いのだけれど、それゆえにアクションの見映えもイマイチ。クライマックスのバトルも、お互い何やってんだか、よく分からなかったです。
アメコミ映画お得意の「エンドロールの最後まで気が抜けない」ラストシーンも、はぁそうですかという感じで…
本家マーベル映画の「現実とリンクしすぎるシリアスな展開」も、かなり息苦しく思えてきてはいるのだけれど、だからといってここまで能天気な展開を見せつけられてもなぁ。
スパイダーマンの続編には期待していますが、ヴェノムの続編は多分観ないと思います。

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
medusa, wronged and accused,
has walked out of the myth,
to the reality of our times,
in the atmosphere of clouded acceptance.
she is no more the gorgon,
but the wronged beauty
whose wings were clipped,
by the powers of lust.
she is out to avenge
for the wrong done
let's not consider her courageous head
as trophy to be blunted.
and hunt her till she becomes a myth again.
one thing in the myth is right,
even today her anger shimmers,
turning the power that be to stone at her gaze.  check my next post for continuation of this. thanks.

text:
check my previous post please.

i came across this powerful statue by luciano garbati in quartz and was spellbound of the artist's version of the inversion of a myth.

a statue speaks the minds of a billion people. this one screams at you with the urgency of a message delivered at the right time. this should provide courage in time of need. this shatters everything.

though, this was ten years old, maybe, as they say one can't stop an idea whose time has come. medusa has arrived and how?

with that angry gaze, a sword in her left hand and a severed head in her right, a symbolic representation of how wronged feel.

it feels as if the sculptor had inured this version in his mind, his hands looking into the mind chiselled away the rest bringing to life the imagined medusa

text:
83년도 4월호 영레이디에 실린 위안부 할머니 노수복 여사님의 고백수기. 이분이 한국에 오셔서 나눔의 집에 계신지,돌아가셨는지는 모르겠다.
그러나 이번에 화제가 된 위안부 합의 논란을 보며 이 기사를 그냥 넘길수가 없었다.
자신의 정치적 이익을 위해 일제시대 피해자인 국민의 인권을 짓밟은 박정희나 공주님으로서 권리와 혜택은 다 누리고 나라를 쑥대밭으로 만들며 바람의 파이터 만화책이나 쳐보며 본인이 저지른 위안부 졸속합의에 전혀 책임을 안지는 박근혜..
진보와 보수를 떠나 국민과 국익을 최우선으로 하는게 정치이고 민주주의인데 과연 나라가 제대로 돌아가는지 모르겠다.
일제와 대한민국에 의해 두번씩이나 유린당한 위안부 할머니의 인권,성범죄 피해자인 여성의 인권을 돈과 권력,정치적 이익이란 잣대로 짓밟지말자.
그리고 협상과 혐의는 자격과 자질,정통성을 갖춘 지도자가 있는 정부에서 해야 효험과 가치가 있다.쿠테타로 불법적으로 정권 탈취한 아저씨나 국정원 댓글로 대통령이 된 딸이 뭣도 모르고 한 조약이 무슨 효과가 있나?
계약서 작성과 체결도 자격을 갖추지 않는자와 하면 무효라고 하지 않나?
어차피 사람은 확증적 편향과 선택적 노출에 의한 필터버블 현상을 겪으니 자기 편한대로 생각하기 마련이고 설득당하지 않는게 인간이지만..인권은 소중한 것이다.
부디 이번 정부와 외교부가 제대로 대응해서 제대로된 합의와 사과,보상을 받고 적폐 청산을 제대로 하면 좋겠다.
피해자의 아픔과 고통을 모른척하고 피해자가 다 죽으면 문제를 덮어버리고 자연적으로 해결되리라 생각치말자.83년도나 2017년도 지금 현재나 크게 변한게 없는 한국과 일본정부의 태도와 진전이 없는것이 개탄스럽다.83년도의 기사를 34년이 지난 지금 실어도 전혀 어색한게 없을만큼.더 이상 전쟁범죄와 성범죄의 피해자 그녀들의 인권을 유린하지말고 제대로 된 합의와 조치로 한을 풀어주고 눈물을 닦아드리자

how often do we hear “don’t report me to hr! #metoo hahahahaha” on set? to trivialize and mock the movement shows a lack of empathy and insinuation that women aren’t capable of understanding the emotion conveyed in behaviour towards us (in which both the action and telling us “don’t take that the wrong way” can be hyper-patronizing). do perpetrators often consider themselves to be?  of course not, but it’s still up to us to re-examine our internalized misogyny (in any gender) probono.  coming forward and reporting is not some petty plea for power that white men seem to think women now have.  mutual respect should not be  radical concept. *** let’s also knowledge that white men have exponentially more impunity in these cases.

major thanks to @amyschumer and @ashleygraham for their activism and their will to have a legitimately dangerous discussion for the greater good.

text:
i see - a girl whose heart belongs to the ocean on one of the happiest days of her life. taken before she dove right back in after an exhaustive first surf sesh.
you see - a four lettered word you love using to shame girls because they are wearing something you can't - even if they may be the most clothed person on the shore - and you're uncomfortable.
don't worry i've notified the lifeguards to allow sarees for your next visit there. but beware, your stomach will show while mine doesn't. and i'll be there, ready to scream out my four lettered word. love.

text:
history repeats itself and the wise learn from the past to not be yesterdays fool tomorrow.

last year, i was fired from this grocer for standing up to the racist good ol boys (mgmt and their literal nazi customer friend) and reporting sexual harassment from the married with kid, trump obsessed, manager. (they were about to give me a raise, but i got something better that day: my wonderful dog)

i laughed my way home.

i now make 2 to 3 times as much and will be able to ask for more because i'm worth it and not a soul can deny that.

yesterday, i was fired a few days after reporting the sexual harassment (quid pro quo and so on) from two chefs (main one also with a kid and from a deep red state, fired from his last job) and incessant verbal abuse from their boss, and illegal orders to work off the clock and and condoning of the other behavior and pseudo racism by their boss.

i laughed my way out of the door. would you believe they said they were a professional environment?

it's only been a day and i'm having trouble picking between wonderful places with wonderful and kind people that want me to work with them as much as i wish to work with them.

i have a feeling that since this very same pattern of events has repeated itself (third time in 2 years), what may be pictured may soon befall some aspect of where i was illegally ousted.

who's to say? i'm going to work somewhere that doesnt forget my paycheck. (i'm not going to name names unless you have to know just because i don't like to trash even my worst enemies or more than necessary)

you better believe i got the last laugh and cackling like a hyena taking these pictures, too!

#itsthelittlethings #everyvictorycounts #fightracism #redstatesarefullofhate #kitchenconfidential
#cheftalk #cooklife #boh #kitchentalk #industry #cookstories #chefstories #retailsucks #metoo #eeoc #enoughisenough #nomeansno #justiceserved #kitchennightmares

text:
“there could be such cases in sports also,” said wrestler vinesh phogat amidst the #metoo movement storm across the country.

on #metoo

phogat, confessed that she has not experienced any kind of sexual harassment in her career. she says, “i don’t know, but i have not faced any kind of such harassment in my career. i also feel that my sport of wrestling should not have these kind of issues.” “the women who are coming out are courageous. when you [woman] want to bring out these kind of things in the open, many a times your family will stop you from doing, fearing your reputation will be harmed. the country should be able to deal with these kind of issues,” she added.

text:
this racism scale is a tremendous tool to ground a healthy discussion of #raceequity, and pinpoint your personal, group, institutional & structural maturity. 
there has never been one issue, policy, or concern in the united states of america that isn't grounded in & influenced by the myth of white male superiority. not one. not back then. not now. 
the most important questions we all must ask ourselves are:

1. where do i fall on this scale relating to #indigenouspeople?

2. where do i fall on this scale relating to #africanamericans?

think you're #woke? think again. 
think i forgot about your #affinity? think again. 
no matter your identity, every single issue, policy, or concern you have in the united states of america could be resolved by answering those 2 questions & moving further to the lower right. 
if you say love is the answer, i'll say love is that far bottom right corner. 
you can't name one news story or societal ill that couldn't be resolved by creating equity in the way we treat natives, and when i say blacks, i particularly mean the descendants of those who were enslaved. think about it. i'll wait.

tell me. where do you fall on this scale for question 1 & 2? i'll share my past & current in the comments
