text:
in between growing my own business, podcasting, raising my 3 & 6yo’s, studying, housework, dealing with family crises, hanging with friends, reviewing shows, getting on stage myself & all the other stuff that comes with being a full time mum with a full time business & an extremely busy life, i’m not only baking banana bread, i’m somehow fitting in being a pathological stalker & sociopath - as per photo 2. 
i do feel sad for this delusional trainwreck but after 10 years of ridiculous accusations like the one pictured, it’s wearing a bit thin. 
i’ve reached out to him in friendship, attempting to resolve whatever problem he has with me &, in turn, put an end to the nastiness. i even offered him writing work because he appeared to be stuck in a rut & thought he could do with a break. 
i’ve had poor judgment as far as this mess goes. i’ve owned that, however, i’ve never threatened suicide & i don’t have an abusive bone in my body. i have no idea who his friends are & i don’t have the time, energy or inclination to stalk his social media or his home. he’s simply not that interesting. 
from what i’ve heard, this self-professed anti-feminist uses me (and his made up story) to get his #metoo moment which brings him the attention he craves & gives weight to his anti-feminist views. 
our history is horribly complicated but we both played an equal role in the madness. i have apologised, he has not. however, he accepted my apology years ago & everything seemed ok. as far as his accusation about me showing up to his house goes - the idiot invited me & i left the moment he took off his pants & tried to kiss me - twice! 2 of his housemates can verify this. 
ages ago i did like a heap of his photos on instagram accidentally. at the time, i was using a bot to like photos with perth hashtags. as soon as i realised what happened, i immediately added his account to the blacklist (don’t bot, it’s dumb).
anyway, this guy needs the right support & i hope he finds it. he is a victim. not a victim of my creation, but his own. i did absolutely nothing to trigger this latest attack. please ignore & block this person if you come across him. but be nice, he is obviously quite fragile 🖤

text:
i had an amazing time yesterday, but i am absolutely bone weary and wiped out today. i can’t believe i pushed through three decades of my life like this; having my energy levels plummet after an event and then not even allowing myself time to decompress from the sensory and social overload because no one else seemed similarly affected.

the only reason i lasted yesterday evening is because eventually i was able to retreat to a quiet corner for the last few hours. this morning i even made it to the post-wedding barbecue. i don’t know why this tradition exists, if it’s just a new zealand thing or if it happens everywhere. i can’t understand why the bride and groom would want to organise yet another gathering the day after something as high maintenance as a wedding.

almost no one has been more understanding of my needs than my partner’s group of friends. i didn’t expect this from them, i’ve always known them to be a bunch of very typical kiwi blokes. they have taken a lot of initiative making sure events are accessible to me post diagnosis and that i’m never pressured to stay longer than i can. it’s really sweet.

i took a while to fall asleep when i got back, that happens sometimes when i’m overloaded and need sleep the most. when i finally did sleep i had an awful dream about an email from an hr lady.

complex traumas operate like that, the most mundane and unremarkable of occurrences trigger all manner of threat detection and fight or flight responses. i woke up with my heart beating strangely, upset that something like panic over emails had reached me here.

i retreated back to the sea this afternoon. an attempt to douse ashes that evidently haven’t finished smouldering.

text:
women’s reproductive health has always been a passion of mine. i wanted to create a community for brown women to talk about reproductive health and sex education because we did not have a space for that growing up, and still don’t. i approached zuni with the idea to make this happen and she jumped right on board. working at planned parenthood, i realized there was a distinct difference in health literacy regarding reproductive health. education about reproductive and sexual health topics are lacking in the south asian community. let’s talk about the taboo topics in our community, let’s engage in conversations about topics the brown aunties don’t want us to talk about. let’s end the stigma. 
go follow @thescarletjournal to learn more and leave a comment about what we can discuss!
#unveilthetruth #thescarletjournal

text:
this moment- the 21st century has been one of the most controversial eras affecting a huge part of society. from teen suicide, cyber-bullying, insecurity with body image leading to intensifying surgeries and possibly death, racial segregation and not having our given equal rights just because of color, plus sexual assault has made an enormous impact to our people and an ultimate tragedy. this needs to stop and it starts by one person, so here we are giving our part. remember it could be anyone around you and you don’t know it. be kind to everyone and anyone you meet because i promise you kindness always gives back. “i cannot change the world, but i can cast a stone to create a ripple.”
-mother teresa🦋🙏🏽 i would like to thank my incredible group for bringing this thought to life. it wouldn’t have been possible without you guys, until next year!✨ #stopteensuicide #nobullying #youarebeautiful #perfect #equal #rights #startsbyone #bekind #life #kindness #changetheworld #metoo #timesup

text:
to everyone who sent support in response to my ig stories, thank you. my heart was beating so fast last night every time i fired off my replies. it beat fast when i shared the screenshots here on ig and again when i made a public post on fb (because the original one was removed). it was scary defending myself in a public setting. but i wasn’t standing up for just myself—i was standing up for women everywhere.
.
several people encouraged me to do more. call out his full name, tell his wife, tell his boss. i couldn’t do it. because even though he did something offensive, i still took his feelings and livelihood into consideration. and also, because i feared retaliation. see, this is a challenge women face that men don’t even have to think about.
.
i am happy i was able to speak my peace, and what’s more, i am happy to have this platform to help educate and promote change. even though the original fb post was removed, along with my last reply to him, i hope he saw what i said. i hope he realizes the gravity of his actions and recognized his ignorance. i hope he grows from this. because defending unwarranted and inappropriate emojis is basically a gateway drug. it’s a step before d*** pics, and if it’s not called out, worse forms of sexual harassment are sure to follow.
.
to all the men who stood with me today: i am beyond grateful for you. “behind every woke man is an exhausted feminist.” please continue keeping your friends (and strangers) in check, and don’t let bad behavior slide. help them grow. every single woman in your life will benefit!
.
to all my ladies: don’t be afraid to stand up for yourself! call out anyone who makes you feel uncomfortable. and also, support other women. we have enough men out there who still think it’s okay to gaslight and harass us; we do not need to add to it. #metoo

text:
today i found a roach in the closet. a little one. but a freaking cockroach! and now i wanna die. yeah, ridiculous, right? i know. i just can't think about it or think about how to clean everything in there. and of course, i have to clean, right ocd? well, actually, ocd want to burn everything, but we won't do this. i feel dizzy, sad, mad, lost and in panic. and my back muscles... you don't wanna know how it hurts. because it always hurts pretty bad when i'm stressed. and i can't go to my bedroom without feeling too much pain. 
i just wanna run away or die because i don't know how to deal with everything.

text:
other people can’t tell you what you can have, other people don’t get to tell you who you can be. .

take massive action not tomorrow or the next day or when the timing is right but right now!... today!! to get you to your goal. .

anything that you want in life, anything that’s worth having, you have got to do it yourself. .

nobody is going to care about your dreams as much as you do.  but you have to have a plan first. .

so start with a goal and be all in!! a guess what?? its going to get hard, but you don’t give up on yourself.  don’t give up on your dreams. .

you’re capable of whatever you set your mind to.  so make it amazing! .

take a leap of faith!  jump!  it’s only when we risk everything that we truly understand who we were meant to be. .

girl, listen to me!! i’ve walked through it and ended up on the other-side.  i can’t do life for you  but i can do life with you. 
you’re not alone.  #getafterit

text:
when i was launching my clothing line in the spring, @cbtrn was recommended to me as photographer. i had never worked with him personally but liked him at events i was at. on set he was highly professional, but he also would’ve had no choice because he was never alone with models and models were prepped by myself and my team.

i’m so sickened to learn that this very trust and community exposure was used to trick women into shoots alone with him where he could start his pattern of assault escalation. this is a predator. read @gigisplendid and @cerclecheung for their stories and numerous others on the thread.

i felt very trusting of him after my shoot. i would’ve recommended him! i want to share what i did as a business owner today with this information, in case it helps others in my position. this is by no means the only or the right reaction, just what makes sense to me. i reached out to my models and shoot team first thing to tell them about it and ask how they felt about the photos now. there was support to keep the photos up since i paid for them and remove his credits. i have done this. i have made a decision to not move forward posting more of these because unfortunately i will associate them with a heinous person. although i straight up can’t afford it, i’m looking into a new shoot because it’s important to me, which my models have graciously offered to once again participate in.

this stirred up some real emotion for me. towards the end of college, i was assaulted in a situation where i felt extremely trusting and was very vulnerable. instead of the reaction i’d always told myself i would have (kick their ass) i instead froze, and deflected and eventually just gave in & up hoping it would be over soon. i had only slept with 1 person, my college boyfriend, and i felt so angry that this was next. angry at myself. i felt so ashamed and so stupid and that i had actually been in control and failed. i didn’t even define it as assault because i didn’t have a reference for it. to this day, only a handful of people know this and it’s almost 15 years later. this was hard to share, but i hope this encourages more people to feel they can speak out. #metoo

text:
what defines you?
a selfie is taken in your best moments. through your own control of how you would like to be perceived as opposed to who you actually are. 
you fear others photographing you because it breaks the illusion of your own idea of yourself. 
easier said than done, but let go and embrace your whole being. especially through somebody else’s eyes.

text:
well, and wow....that’s been an extremely full on 24 hours in henley on thames!!! such a great night at hotel du vin tonight for my henley book launch. seeing familiar friendly faces was quite overwhelming...but equally amazing.....tonight was probably one of my toughest presentations; very real and powerful.

my message in my self help book is clear. are you living in your truth having faced your fears? do you know what your voice says?

let don’t hold back guide you, gently challenge you to give you hope (hold on pain ends) and free yourself from the shackles that have been holding you back.

and of course my biggest thanks goes to my audience and my readers.  the support and love as i step into this new phase of life to give my journey back to others is overwhelming.

text:
i have cried almost every day this week. i say this to remind both myself and all of you that it is okay to not be perfect. it is okay to listen to the sadness of your soul. our hearts need to be heard and acknowledged to release what they are carrying. 💕

november has always had this affect on me. it’s as though i’m preparing for the winter, shedding and letting go of everything that i am carrying. 🥀🥀🥀 by releasing my tears and allowing myself to feel, this year can to come to a close and a new cycle of growth can begin. 🌹🌹🌹

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non
